<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="295" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,261,158,184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Garcia-Beltran" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Britton &amp; P. Wilson" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[289,740,159,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="pinnatum" variety="savannarum">
<emphasis box="[289,539,159,185]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Cenostigma pinnatum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[602,740,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">savannarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Garcia-Beltran" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Garcia-Beltran" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[1007,1370,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="pinnatum" variety="oblongifolium">
<emphasis box="[1007,1150,159,185]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">C. pinnatum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1213,1370,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">oblongifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for its leaves with generally broader leaflets, 
<quantity box="[581,704,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" unit="cm" value="2.05" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="1.3">1.3-2.8 cm</quantity>
(vs. 
<quantity box="[764,891,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" unit="cm" value="1.3" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="0.8">0.8-1.8 cm</quantity>
), with 10-12 secondary veins on each side of its midvein (vs. 6-9), inflorescence axes 
<quantity box="[557,683,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.46" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.1199999999999999" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" unit="cm" value="14.6" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="11.2">11.2-18 cm</quantity>
long (vs. 
<quantity box="[795,897,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.75" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" unit="cm" value="7.75" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.5">6.5-9 cm</quantity>
) and peduncles ca. 
<quantity box="[1116,1195,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
(vs. 
<quantity box="[1250,1342,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3-7 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="295" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,403,266,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Lectotypification:</emphasis>
—In the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authority="Britton" authorityName="Britton" box="[653,1027,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Poincianella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="savannarum">
<emphasis box="[653,939,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Poincianella savannarum</emphasis>
Britton
</taxonomicName>
, the herbarium where the type is found is not mentioned, so reference is made to a complete collection and not to a single specimen, so that all duplicates are considered 
<typeStatus box="[267,365,339,365]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">syntypes</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[381,608,338,364]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" refId="ref4755" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code). Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">Turland &amp; al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 40 Note 1). 
<bibRefCitation author="Barreto, A." box="[814,982,338,365]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" pagination="18" refId="ref4082" refString="Barreto, A. (2013) Caesalpiniaceae. In: Greuter, W. &amp; Rankin, R. (Eds.) Flora de la Republica de Cuba. Serie A. Plantas Vasculares. Fasciculo 18. Koeltz Scientific Books, Konigstein." type="book chapter" year="2013">Barreto (2013)</bibRefCitation>
recognizes the material deposited in NY as a 
<typeStatus box="[187,285,374,400]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">holotype</typeStatus>
of this name, but such designation cannot be considered effective lectotypification, since as of 
<date pageId="4" pageNumber="295" value="2001-01-01">January 1, 2001</date>
, the phrase “designated here” or an equivalent is required (
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[908,1135,410,436]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" refId="ref4755" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code). Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[1007,1066,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 7.11). For this reason, 
<taxonomicName authority="Britton" authorityName="Britton" box="[136,511,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Poincianella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="savannarum">
<emphasis box="[136,424,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Poincianella savannarum</emphasis>
Britton
</taxonomicName>
is lectotyped here with the material suggested by 
<bibRefCitation author="Barreto, A." box="[1072,1240,446,473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" pagination="18" refId="ref4082" refString="Barreto, A. (2013) Caesalpiniaceae. In: Greuter, W. &amp; Rankin, R. (Eds.) Flora de la Republica de Cuba. Serie A. Plantas Vasculares. Fasciculo 18. Koeltz Scientific Books, Konigstein." type="book chapter" year="2013">Barreto (2013)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
